On Sun, Jan 15, 2006 at 01:59:53PM +0300, Evgeniy Polyakov wrote: > > Are you sure sed and awk are good for kernel? > Above string parsing eventually will end up in tricky bugs. > What about following: > > tfm = crypto_tfm_alloc("deflate", flags); > err = tfm->setup(&user_provided_deflate_parameters); > > int deflate_setup(void *data) > { > struct deflate_setup *s = data; > > ... setup compression parameters from user's structure ... > > return 0; > }
